<body><p>GE.10-12228  (E)    190310 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Thirteenth session 
</b>Agenda item 9 
<b>Racism, racial discrimination, xenophobia and related  
forms of intolerance, follow-up to and implementation  
of the Durban Declaration and Programme of Action 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Nigeria (on behalf of the African Group): draft resolution 
</b></p>
<p><b>  13/&#8230;  
Elaboration of complementary standards to the International 
Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination 
</b></p>
<p><i> The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p><i> Recalling</i> its decision 3/103 of 8 December 2006 on the elaboration of 
complementary standards to the International Convention on the Elimination of All Forms 
of Racial Discrimination and the creation of the Ad Hoc Committee for this purpose, 
</p>
<p> <i>Underlining</i> the imperative need to elaborate the legal instruments required to 
complement and fill the existing substantive gaps in the Convention in order to strengthen 
and update international instruments against racism, racial discrimination, xenophobia and 
related intolerance in all their aspects, 
</p>
<p> <i>Underlining</i> <i>also</i> the need for the Ad Hoc Committee to accomplish its mandate, 
</p>
<p> 1. <i>Requests</i> the Ad Hoc Committee on the elaboration of complementary 
standards to elaborate additional protocols to the International Convention on the 
Elimination of All Forms of Racial Discrimination in a structured manner; 
</p>
<p> 2. <i>Decides</i> that the Ad Hoc Committee shall convene its third session from 30 
November to 10 December 2010; 
</p>
<p> 3. <i>Requests</i> the Chairperson-Rapporteur of the Ad Hoc Committee to prepare, 
on the basis of inputs already received, a draft additional protocol on cybercrime for 
negotiations scheduled to commence at its third session; 
</p>
<p> 4. <i>Decides</i> to remain seized of this priority issue. 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p> 
</p>
